        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>No. 155 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Chief of Staff</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of the Joint Chiefs of
                        Staff</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MBGAJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McFarland</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-15">15 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary of the Joint Chiefs of
                        Staff</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The following subjects have been mentioned to the President as likely to be
                    brought up before the forthcoming tripartite meeting.</p>
                <pb facs="0307" n="175" xml:id="pg_175"/>
                <p>Will you please, as a matter of urgency endeavor to obtain from the appropriate
                    agencies of the Joint Chiefs of Staff brief but pertinent and useful
                    recommendations on these questions that will be useful to the President in
                    preparing himself for the conference?— <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Dismemberment of Germany.<note n="1" xml:id="d155fn1">See <ref target="#d332">documents Nos. 332</ref> and <ref target="#d514">514</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Internationalization of the Ruhr and the Saar.<note n="2" xml:id="d155fn2">See <ref target="#d403">document No.
                                403</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Arrangements to get coal for other European countries.<note n="3" xml:id="d155fn3">See <ref target="#d418">document No.
                                418</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Exchange of commodities between zones of occupation—food from the
                            Russian zone for other areas in Germany.<note n="4" xml:id="d155fn4">See
                                    <ref target="#d419">document No. 419</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Civil government in Germany—when should it be established and
                                how?<note n="5" xml:id="d155fn5">See <ref target="#d333">document
                                    No. 333</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>What will be the banking arrangements in Germany? What money will be
                            used, and what exchange arrangements made?<note n="6" xml:id="d155fn6">See <ref target="#d334">document No. 334</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>7.</label>
                        <item>Establishment of a unified agreed propaganda in Germany.<note n="7" xml:id="d155fn7">See <ref target="#d335">document No.
                                335</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>8.</label>
                        <item>What disposition, distribution, should be made of the German Fleet and
                            captured German merchant ships?<note n="8" xml:id="d155fn8">See <ref target="#d391">documents Nos. 391</ref> and <ref target="#d392">392</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, and <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#d1005">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, document No. 1005</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>9.</label>
                        <item>What should [the] American attitude be toward the selection and
                            treatment of war criminals?<note n="9" xml:id="d155fn9">See <ref target="#d396">document No. 396</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>10.</label>
                        <item>When should we agree to making the peace treaty with <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName> and what terms should be agreeable
                            to the United States?<note n="10" xml:id="d155fn10">See <ref target="#d465">document No. 465</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">W[<hi rend="smallcaps">illiam</hi>] D. L[<hi rend="smallcaps">eahy</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
